# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  03 - PUT & PATCH Requests
#
#  PUT   → Full replacement. You MUST send ALL fields.
#          Missing fields are removed from the resource.
#
#  PATCH → Partial update. Send only the fields you want to change.
#          All other fields stay as they are.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com

# ── PUT — Full replacement ────────────────────────────────────

### Full Update Post 1 (PUT)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/posts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Updated Title",
  "body": "This completely replaces the post body.",
  "userId": 1
}


### Full Update User 1 (PUT)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "John Updated",
  "username": "johnupdated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "phone": "555-9999",
  "website": "updated.dev"
}


# ── PATCH — Partial update ────────────────────────────────────

### Patch Post Title Only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/posts/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Only the Title Changed"
}


### Mark Todo as Completed
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/todos/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "completed": true
}


### Patch User Email Only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "new.email@example.com"
}
